The paper deals with a robot navigating in a grid and constructing a structure, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The use of a deterministic finite automaton to accomplish the task suggests a focus on algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and computational complexity (cs.CC). The problem of constructing a compact structure also involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques.
